						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in front of the Duggavva temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 1153-54 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śrīmukha, Āshāḍha ba. 5, Monday. Palaeographically the record may be assigned to the 12th century A.D. The said cyclic year may therefore be taken to correspond to 1153-54 A.D., when the other details correspond to July 12, the weekday being Sunday.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land to a Jaina temple. The epigraph is damaged and the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
